Femi Adesina, the Special Adviser on Media and Publicity to President Buhari, has said that Nigerians are lucky to have a leader like his principal at a time like this. Adesina stated this via his social media handle while dismissing attempts to pitch him against his boss, the president. According to him, he is a Buharist. In a post on his Twitter handle, Adesina wrote “A quote from mischief-makers is making the rounds, ascribed to me. I just dey laugh. I am a Buharist any day, no apologies, and I believe the president and I believe the president is leading the country well. In fact, we are lucky to him at a time like this. All attempts to demonize me will fail.” source A presidential spokesperson, Femi Adesina, has released the statement below attacking an editor of Thisday newspaper over an article critical of President Muhammadu Buhari. Mr Adesina said he was responding to the article by editor Shaka Momodu titled ‘The General is Divider-in-Chief. Read Mr Adesina’s full statement below. Shaka Momodu:… January 13, 2020 In "News" By Edith ike-Eboh Enugu (Mmaku) -  Mr Femi Adesina, Special Adviser to the President on Media and Publicity, has been conferred with the traditional title of Nwanne Di Na Mba (A brother in another land) Mmaku Kingdom, Enugu State. Adesina received the chieftaincy title during the 1st Grand Ofala festival… January 3, 2018 In "Top Stories" ABUJA (Sundiata Post) - The Special Adviser to President Muhammadu Buhari on Media and Publicity, Femi Adesina, has disclosed that his principal would not request any journalist to "kill" stories for him. Adesina said instead of doing that, the administration would rather encourage newsmen to run stories that would critically… August 16, 2015 In "News"